  "intent": "For this Tecan Cortisol ELISA protocol, you'll be working with the working plate in slot 2, samples in slot 1, reagents in the deep well plate at slot 4, and wash buffer in slot 5 using the heater shaker module. Start by mixing the reagents twice, then transfer your samples and reagents to the working plate before closing the heater-shaker latch and shaking at s_speed RPM during the incubation pauses. You'll need to manually move the ELISA plate to the shaker after the initial incubation, then proceed with the sample transfers from A1 to A1 positions, washing steps, and additional reagent additions with 2x mixing between each transfer. Finally, open the latch and move the ELISA plate to the reader for analysis.",
